value.0: Primly dressed and with an almost haughty demeanour, Lieutenant Marbury Grant stands surveying the atrium of Outpost Hope with a blandly attentive expression.
"Yes? Have you thinned out their numbers? They have been menacing the supply convoys..."

"So you did. Good job, recruit. Now, it is expected that a soldier of the Republic should know how to comport himself. How to act, how to behave. What to do. To follow the laws. To abide by the ideals of our Republic." He draws out a data chit, and holds it out. "There's a training droid I designed. It's in the mess hall. Insert this into it, and it will ask you a series of questions. It will test you ability to make decisions, and your judgment skills. It's not much, but it is still a basic judgment aptitude test that I expect all members of the Special Forces to be capable of passing."

"Good. Now, unless you already have a squad that you are joining, you shall be placed under Cresh Company, and under my direct command. For now, you are permitted to conduct independent operations, to further your own unique training and abilities. You will be called upon if needed for operations, and you may avail yourself of Outpost Hope's training facilities in the meantime as well. This is your keycard. If you have need of anything, use the Republic's internal communications channel to contact me."

"Very good. Return to me the data-chit. You are now ready to take your enlistment. Make what preparations you may wish to and return to me. Remember, reaffirming such an oath is not to be done lightly."

// OOC Warning: Joining a faction is not to be done lightly. Please note that betraying a faction could lead to consequences that may result in being demoted, expelled from the faction, or even permanent death.
"Yes? Have you thinned out their numbers? They have been menacing the supply convoys..."

An assessing look, followed by a curt nod. "The Republic is governed by the Senate from Coruscant, and represents trillions and trillions of lives over a thousand, thousand worlds within the galaxy. It serves to protect the cherished ideals that had bound it; freedom, security, liberty, and the rights of sentients to live as equals, to live freely. That is what every man and uniform in this outpost serve to protect, and what you should consider doing yourself, if, that is, you make the cut."

"Outpost Hope is commanded by Captain Tyche Vanicus. It is the primary Republic installation and garrison on Viscara, and we work with Czerka to ensure that the Sith Empire does not claim this world and its people. We sometimes lend aid to operations abroad, such as in Corellia or elsewhere. More than that, you either don't have the requisite security clearance to know or you aren't learning through the appropriate channels."
An assessing look. "You may refer to me as sir."

An assessing look. "To serve as a soldier in the Galactic Republic is to serve in the greatest and largest fighting force in the galaxy. The Republic safeguards and safevouches the freedom and security of its people against monsters such as the so-called Darth Malak. Across a thousand, thousand stars are the Republic's worlds, and guarding these are countless men. Enlist, and we will train you, teach you, arm you, to become one of these brave men and women who would protect the Galactic Republic and all it stands for. Indeed, for exceptionally talented individuals with the rare potential, the Republic Navy has instituted a new Special Forces Scheme, which grants both extraordinary latitude in how you serve."

"Indeed! If you enlist under the Special Forces Scheme, you will either first be placed under Cresh Company, or directly in-processed into an existing Squad if you have the recommendation of the Squad Leader and my permission. You will be permitted to conduct independent operations under the aegis of the Republic, while participating in some of the most intense and important missions and operations in our war against the brittle tyranny of the Sith Empire."

"I have high standards for those seeking to serve in the Republic, especially in the Special Services Scheme. These are the elites, the ones who can wade into the heat of the thickest fire and come out alive with the mission accomplished. You want in, you shall have to prove to me that you are worthy. Reconnaissance units have been reporting sightings of increased raivor activities around the mountain valleys. Thin out their numbers, and come back to me when you have done so."

// OOC Warning: Please do not accept or continue on this quest unless you do not belong to any faction and you are genuine in intending for your character to join the Republic. If your intentions are to infiltrate the Republic or to betray it at a later date, please contact a DM first.

"Ambitious, are you? Well, particularly promising and extraordinary enlistees who demonstrate great leadership skills and maturity may be invited to join the Wartime Officer Scheme, where one with the appropriate skills and expertise may become an Officer Cadet. It is an arduous and incredibly difficult journey to go from a Cadet to being commissioned as an Ensign, and we will be judging your actions and behaviour far harsher and hold you to higher standards than anyone else if you are an Officer Cadet."
An assessing look. "You may refer to me as sir."
"Sir, about enlisting..."
"I have done it, sir."
"Uh, no."
"Yes, sir. I am ready to take the training quiz, sir."
"I am on it, sir."
"Sir, I have taken my enlistment oath."
"Thank you, sir!"
"Sir, I have completed the training quiz."
"Let me think about this..."
Return the data-chit. "I am ready, sir."
"Sir, about enlisting..."
"I am on it, sir."
"Can you tell me more about the Republic, sir?"
"Can you tell me more about Outpost Hope, sir?"
"Yes, sir."
"Can you tell me more about the Republic?"
"S-Sorry, sir."
"Kriff that."
"Can you tell me more about enlisting in the Republic, sir?"
"Special Forces Scheme, sir?"
"I want to enlist, sir."
"On second thoughts, maybe not."
"Sir, yes, sir."
"How can I become an officer myself, sir?"
"Not for me, thanks."
"Not for me, thanks."
"Can you tell me more about enlisting in the Republic?"
"S-Sorry, sir."
"Kriff that."
